      "status": "done",
      "title": "Fix symlink escape in Cursor read transcript fallback",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "security",
        "cursor-sdk",
        "transcript"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "src/cursor-tool-transcript.ts",
        "test/cursor-tool-transcript.test.ts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "src/cursor-tool-transcript.ts:194-205 re-reads empty Cursor read results after only a textual inside-cwd check.",
        "src/cursor-tool-transcript.ts:172-174 checks relative path text, while statSync/openSync follow symlinks.",
        "test/cursor-tool-transcript.test.ts:43-68 covers sensitive/direct outside files but not symlink-to-outside paths."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add a regression test for an in-workspace symlink pointing to an outside file.",
        "Resolve real paths for cwd and target before inside-cwd and sensitivity checks, or reject symlinks with lstatSync.",
        "Run npm test and npm run typecheck."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Started by agent to fix symlink escape in Cursor read transcript fallback.",
        "Implemented realpath-based preview validation for cwd and target before opening fallback read preview. Added symlink-to-outside regression test. Validated with npm test -- test/cursor-tool-transcript.test.ts, npm test, npm run typecheck. Reviewer subagent reported no material findings."
      ],
