      "id": "RQ-0007",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Reduce local re-read fallback risk in Cursor tool transcripts",
      "priority": "low",
      "tags": [
        "transcript",
        "correctness",
        "cursor-sdk"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "src/cursor-tool-transcript.ts",
        "test/cursor-tool-transcript.test.ts",
        "README.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "src/cursor-tool-transcript.ts:218-253 fills empty Cursor read content by reading the current local file.",
        "That preview may show content Cursor did not actually see if the file changed after Cursor's read."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Decide whether to remove local read fallback or label it explicitly as a local preview at replay time.",
        "Adjust transcript and native display output accordingly.",
        "Update tests and docs for empty Cursor read-result behavior.",
        "Run npm test and npm run typecheck."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "Started by agent to reduce local re-read fallback risk in Cursor tool transcripts.",
        "Kept safe local fallback read previews but labeled them as transcript-time local previews when Cursor read result content is unavailable. Native read display uses same label. README documents the semantics. Validated with npm test -- test/cursor-tool-transcript.test.ts, npm test, npm run typecheck. Reviewer subagent reported no material findings."
      ],
